{"TopicId":212866,"ForumId":119,"TopicTitle":"Very Kerbal design choices at the KSC","CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T02:03:59Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T02:03:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEverything about the design of the Kerbal Space Center campus screams \u0022Made by Kerbals\u0022...Keeping in mind that most rockets are launching east, here are a few instances I\u0027ve noticed of things being designed to be as hazardous as possible:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Launch sites directly downrange of one another\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-R\u0026amp;D/Training/etc. is directly downrange of multiple launch sites\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Aircraft control tower should theoretically have a good view in all directions, but is blocked by the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E right next to it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-All landing pads west of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E: If a booster is performing a RTLS to one of these pads, it must fly directly over the Tracking Station and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drakenred65","CreatedById":154503,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T02:45:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose landing pads have me wondering if we\u0027re actually using them for that or if it\u0027s just cosmetic\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T03:21:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224243195\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022212866\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677379517\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154503\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Drakenred65\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n35 minutes ago, Drakenred65 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose landing pads have me wondering if we\u0027re actually using them for that or if it\u0027s just cosmetic\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWho\u0027s to stop you?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T03:23:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224243195\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022212866\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677379517\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154503\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Drakenred65\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, Drakenred65 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose landing pads have me wondering if we\u0027re actually using them for that or if it\u0027s just cosmetic\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe difference is..?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Chilkoot","CreatedById":175911,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T05:17:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t believe those circular areas near the runway are landing pads, but rather berths for planes as you\u0027d see near, say, a military runway.\u00A0 I\u0027ll see if I can find some supporting images.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T06:56:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224243134\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022212866\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677377039\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cubinator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, cubinator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEverything about the design of the Kerbal Space Center campus screams \u0022Made by Kerbals\u0022...Keeping in mind that most rockets are launching east, here are a few instances I\u0027ve noticed of things being designed to be as hazardous as possible:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Launch sites directly downrange of one another\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-R\u0026amp;D/Training/etc. is directly downrange of multiple launch sites\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Aircraft control tower should theoretically have a good view in all directions, but is blocked by the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E right next to it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-All landing pads west of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E: If a booster is performing a RTLS to one of these pads, it must fly directly over the Tracking Station and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds fun to me. But I agree that the Aircraft Control Tower should be moved. Also we need a road to the docks and some bridges.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-02-26T06:58:43Z\u0022 title=\u002202/26/2023 06:58  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 26, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Vl3d\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hutsul228","CreatedById":222672,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T07:00:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn ksp 1 it\u00A0was like Kennedy sc. In ksp2 it sounds more like Boca Chica.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-02-26T07:00:22Z\u0022 title=\u002202/26/2023 07:00  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 26, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Hutsul228\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drakenred65","CreatedById":154503,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T16:36:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224243251\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022212866\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677381822\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe difference is..?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe difference being if they plan stage recovery being a thing.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224243246\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022212866\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677381688\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cubinator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, cubinator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWho\u0027s to stop you?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNothing. I was just wondering on if it would be automatic once you do the first booster recovery for a given design or if they plan on something like that one recovery mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}